HEADWORD: Fragmentary
<hw>Frag"men*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>fragmentaire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Composed of fragments,
or broken pieces; disconnected; not complete or entire.</def>
<rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Composed of the fragments of
other rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fragmentation</ent>⟦br⟧
